http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/%E2%80%987-Hills-Marathon%E2%80%99-on-Oct.-23/article14642230.ece

 After Vizag and Amaravati, Disease Eradication through Education and Prevention (DEEP) has announced to conduct marathon in Tirupati to help people adapt to and motivate them to follow a healthy lifestyle.Named as '7 Hills Marathon' after the famed seven hills of Tirumala, the event will be held on Oct 23 at 6 am in the categories of 21.1 km (half marathon) and 10km, 5km and 3km. The district administration, police and civic officials have been involved in the process and are fully geared to make it a success. According to the organisers Madhu Vasepalli and Rakesh Kalapala, founders of DEEP, Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu would take part in the prestigious event. For further information and registration, log on to www.7hillsmarathon.com.